    "HAP LAI Be Thankful Every Day By Chaplain R E Jenkins Yestcrdav we celebrated one of the most significant of all our national holidays The spirit of Thanksgiving could be and should be ingrained within us throughout the year for a thankful person is the most for tunate of all humans He is rich beyond measure You remember the cripple at the Pool of Bethesda as recorded by John in the New Testament Here was a man who for thirty eight years had lain on his bed of pain He believed that if for but one brief moment he could bathe In the rutiled waters of the pool his useless legs would be made strong enough to walk on The odds were against him Too many people rushed to the wa ters edge ahead of him every time the waters began to ripple He had no relative or friend to lift him bodily into the pool The mass of suffering humanity about him surged over and around him at the first sign of the rippling of the waters They were all bent on one purpose to cure them The Navys Oldest Newspaper Established 1901 More than 7000 Rader IT S"
